Package org.neo4j.values.utils

Class TemporalValueWriterAdapter<E extends Exception>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.neo4j.values.storable.ValueWriter.Adapter<E>
      • org.neo4j.values.utils.TemporalValueWriterAdapter<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the error type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ValueWriter<E>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NativeIndexKey, PropertyStore.PropertyBlockValueWriter
    public abstract class TemporalValueWriterAdapter<E extends Exception>
extends ValueWriter.Adapter<E>
    A ValueWriter that defines format for all temporal types, except duration. Subclasses will not be able to override methods like writeDate(LocalDate). They should instead override writeDate(long) that defines how LocalDate is serialized.

    Primary purpose of this class is to share serialization format between property store writer and schema indexes.
